@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About — HD2 Armorer</PageTitle>

<div class="about-page">
    <h2 class="about-heading">About</h2>

    <section class="about-section">
        <p>
            I wanted a quick way to find armor that protects against fire — or gas, acid, or explosives —
            without clicking through every piece in the game. This is that tool.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Owned armor tracking</h3>
        <p>
            Owned and display settings are stored locally in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>
            under the keys <code>hd2armorer.owned</code>, <code>hd2armorer.showOwnedBadges</code>,
            and <code>hd2armorer.showOwnedOnly</code>. This data never leaves your device and is not
            shared with anyone. Clearing your browser data will remove it.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Created by standing on the shoulders of giants, thank you:</h3>
        <p>
            Armor data and images are sourced from
            <ExternalLink Href="https://github.com/Selenestica/hd2-random-strat">hd2-random-strat</ExternalLink>
            by <strong>Selenestica</strong>. This project would not exist without their work.
        </p>
        <p>
            The <em>Acclimated</em> passive icon is hand-traced from Helldivers 2 game assets by
            <ExternalLink Href="https://helldivers.wiki.gg/wiki/User:Dogo314">Dogo314</ExternalLink>
            via the <ExternalLink Href="https://helldivers.wiki.gg">Helldivers Wiki</ExternalLink>.
            Used with attribution under Arrowhead Game Studios' EULA.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Resources</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <ExternalLink Href="https://helldivers.wiki.gg/wiki/Helldivers_2">Helldivers Wiki</ExternalLink>
                — authoritative reference for armor stats, passives, and acquisition
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
